TTS
<*,*,*,*>:  Begin by cooking the spaghetti to “al dente” in salted water. Then, chop the guanciale into cubes and, adding just a touch of olive oil, crisp it up lightly on medium heat for about 7-10 minutes. Now, Crack the eggs into a bowl and add the 1 cup of pecorino. Quite easy, huh?
